to the ground. The horseman fortunately was not mounted
at the time, and having his gun in his hand, the bear
instantly disappeared in the depths of the forest.

On the 5th of September we crossed a defile, which had
been passed shortly before by a numerous troop of horsemen.
Whether they were allies or enemies, we had no
means to discover. I will here observe, that in these
immense solitudes, although the howling of wolves, the
hissing of venomous serpents, the roaring of the tiger and
