of the Arkansas and Red rivers. In 1836 he made his well-known voyage
to the sources of the Mississippi, and in 1839 explored the Missouri, crossing over
to the Red River Valley, being accompanied on this expedition by John C. Frémont.
The following years, until his death in 1843, he was employed in government
service at Washington.       Ed.



